{
  "text": "1,3-5 However, outcomes have been improved by other procedures for exclusion of an ARSA and Kommerell diverticulum, including an elephant trunk with endovascular completion, FET, transposition or bypass of the subclavian artery to the carotid artery, and ARSA occlusion using an occlusion device. [CITATION_1] Endovascular repair using a stent graft with or without an ARSA bypass or transposition has recently become a common procedure for ARSA; however, a limited proximal landing zone may lead to a type I endoleak. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] The optimal procedure to use for repair should be selected according to the patient's anatomy.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8922789",
